Drinking can kill the smell.
I try some pieces.
If you can avoid passing it near your nose, it’s not bad; it’s not much different than a portion of sushi you’ve traveled a few miles by bus.
Rakfisk is a product that comes from a very different time, in which poverty plagued Norway and in which, before refrigeration existed, fish was stored during the autumn submerged in water and salt in airtight barrels.
Later, in the middle of winter, when it is already well fermented, it is taken out and, obviously with the senses inactive due to alcohol, it is eaten.
Just a generation ago, thousands of Norwegians were forced to leave their country in search of work, and migrated mainly to the United States.
