Basketball globetrotters Hector "Hetin" Reyes was more than 60 years linked to the sport of tabloncillo and, thanks to him, traveled the entire world.
Few people in Puerto Rico have a mental recollection of local basketball history as broad as Héctor "Hetin" Reyes.
And is that before a stroke confined him to a wheelchair in 2008, Reyes was immersed in the sport for more than 60 years, whether as a player of minor categories, player of the National Superior Basketball, proxy and leader in the BSN with the Bayamón Cowboys or president of the Basketball Federation.
