“Basketball has been my life.”
Reyes does not exaggerate in making that assertion.
The walls of his house, almost all decorated with photos and memorabilia that denote his extensive career, attest to this.
Bayamon in the heart
Of all, the ones he treasures with the most emotion are those that recall his time with the Cowboys from the mid-1950s as a player until 1982, when he turned 15 years old serving as a co-operator or proxy of the franchise.
“Those were my best years, the ones I enjoyed the most because I had the opportunity to be part of eight Cowboys championships since 1967, whether as an attorney, co-manager or manager.
